Full SQL Query

SELECT 
SUM(OD.quantity) AS total_products_sold,
SUM(OD.quantity * P.price) AS total_revenue
FROM Products P
JOIN OrderDetails OD
ON P.product_id = OD.product_id
GROUP BY P.name;


Line-by-Line Meaning
SELECT
SELECT

Meaning:

Used to fetch/display data from database.
1st Line
SUM(OD.quantity) AS total_products_sold


Meaning of Each Word

| Word                | Meaning                                   |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| SUM()               | Adds all values together                  |
| OD                  | Short name (alias) for OrderDetails table |
| quantity            | Quantity column from OrderDetails table   |
| AS                  | Rename column                             |
| total_products_sold | New column name shown in result           |

Simple Meaning
Add all ordered quantities and show as total_products_sold.
Example

If quantities are:

quantity
2
1
3

Then:

2 + 1 + 3 = 6

Result:

total_products_sold
6

=========
2nd Line
SUM(OD.quantity * P.price) AS total_revenue
Meaning of Each Word

| Word          | Meaning            |
| ------------- | ------------------ |
| SUM()         | Add all values     |
| OD.quantity   | Ordered quantity   |
| *             | Multiplication     |
| P.price       | Product price      |
| AS            | Rename column      |
| total_revenue | Result column name |


Simple Meaning
Multiply quantity × price for every product,
then add all amounts together.
Example


| quantity | price | quantity × price |
| -------- | ----- | ---------------- |
| 2        | 50    | 100              |
| 1        | 30    | 30               |


Total Revenue:

100 + 30 = 130
